@vahidhashemian Shouldn't `testPatternUnsubscription` not even need a metadata update to achieve its target state? It'll request one, but even if it got stale metadata, the unsubscription step would still work since it's really just a regex change for that particular case.

Given the way this fails, it seems like it would have to be that the update is getting stale metadata, right? The metadata update in the clients is blocking, so `poll()` wouldn't even return if the request itself was delayed. It looks more like it is getting old (in some of these cases empty) metadata and not recovering. But that also seems pretty weird since most of these tests use a really aggressive `METADATA_MAX_AGE_CONFIG` of `100ms`, so they should be picking up updated metadata really quickly.

If someone is able to reproduce this consistently locally (I've yet to see any of these fail on my laptop), it'd be nice to get some logging on the metadata refreshes to get a better idea of what's happening during one of the failing tests.

A quick fix which doesn't address the problem completely, but which should get the tests passing again would be to do something like this in `ConsumerCoordinator.ensurePartitionAssignment()`:

``` java
        if (subscriptions.partitionsAutoAssigned()) {
            if (subscriptions.hasPatternSubscription())
                client.ensureFreshMetadata();
            ensureActiveGroup();
        }
```

This continues on KIP-4 from the create topics patch (#1489).

